oyees and forward gathered/consolidated information to appropriate Town staff.May fill in or provide backup for other administrative personnel when necessary.Composes and prepares courteous and professionally formatted business-related correspondence, memoranda, and other documents from rough draft or general instructions. Completes necessary standard department forms for supervisor review or submittal of information for internal Town use. Proofreads correspondence and other materials for grammatical correctness and content.Processes department/division mail by opening, date stamping, and distributing to the appropriate personnel in accordance with established procedures. Maintains mailing lists and department mailings as necessary.Maintains an accurate and efficient filing and tracking system by creating new files, removing outdated files for archiving and/or disposition, and sorting, scanning, and filing documents by type and/or subject as appropriate. Utilizes various software and hard files to provide a consistent, organized tracking system, maintaining records in accordance with applicable Florida State Statutes.May perform clerk duties, prepare agendas and compile supporting backup documents and minutes in a manner consistent with Town recordkeeping standards for public meetings such as but not limited to Town Council meetings and other public meetings for Town boards and commissions, which may be held quarterly or otherwise. Ensures timely distribution of backup documentation.Compiles department/division technical and statistical data, prepares and/or maintains various records and reports, checking and proofing for accuracy in accordance with established procedures. Utilizes department-specific software to organize and track related information.May receive and prepare responses to public records requests from the public and/or town personnel in accordance with Florida State Statutes.May prepare appropriate requests, forms, and travel arrangements for department/division personnel.May maintain staf
